summary: [Spoilers] Parallels between a story Bran tells and later events in the show.
title: [Spoilers] Parallels between a story Bran tells and later events in the show.
body:
I’m rewatching the series (again) and I noticed something I hadn’t notice before. I don’t know if anyone has pointed this out before, but in season 3 episode 10 Bran tells the story of the Rat Cook at the Night Fort. The night’s watch cook who served a king a pie filled with his own son, as punishment the Gods transformed the cook into a white rat that would feast on his young, forever hungry. However, the Gods did not punish him for murder but rather for killing a guest in under his roof. Obviously, this is following the Red Wedding and this is alluding to Walder Frey murdering guests under his roof. When Arya takes revenge on Walder Frey she feeds him a pie of made from his sons, he was forced to feed on his young as punishment for murdering guests under his care, just like the Rat Cook.

TLDR; Walder Frey is the Rat Cook being forced to eat his children out of punishment.



Source: http://bit.ly/2MI51Lv

summary: not only is political!jon 100% ooc it’s also a disservice and a disgrace to jon’s entire character we’ve seen time after time...
body:
not only is political!jon 100% ooc it’s also a disservice and a disgrace to jon’s entire character

we’ve seen time after time jon making and standing by his decisions because he is driven by what is right and honorable, and while some of those decisions have been downright stupid, he has stood by them

he saved thousands of wildlings because it was the right thing to do, because the white walkers are a threat, and he died for that decision

also we know for a fact that unlike several other players in this game, jon is not a schemer and has never shown any tendencies of being one

(also most political!jon metas I’ve seen are grossly sexist and misogynist)
